  "execution_target": "cpp",
  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is a logical and work-efficiency mismatch (Category A/C): the current plan pays a large build_joins cost by scanning broad orders ranges and constructing a runtime orders hash table before lineitem probing. This revision uses the selective pre-built orders_custkey_hash to enumerate only orders belonging to BUILDING customers, applies the orderdate predicate before materialization, then switches to a compact orderkey lookup plus partitioned direct-array aggregation during a zonemap-pruned sequential lineitem pass to remove hash-build overhead and hot-path atomic contention.",
  "correctness_anchors": {
    "o_orderdate_cutoff_days_since_epoch": 9204,
    "l_shipdate_cutoff_days_since_epoch": 9204,
    "revenue_formula": "l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)",
